OL,4,C#900,000 for polluting the Diseworth
OL,5,CBrook
OL,7,FA second incident occurred on February
OL,8,F1st, 2022, when excessive pollutants
OL,9,Fwere discharged from the Eastern
OL,10,FSummer Pond, Environment Agency
OL,11,Fofficials said.
OL,13,FThe third and final charge relates to
OL,14,Fan incident on February 4th, 2022,
OL,15,Fwhen regulations were again breached
OL,16,Fwith excessive BOD levels from the
OL,17,FWestern Summer Ponds.
OL,19,FAll violations were contrary to
OL,20,FRegulation 38(2) of the Environmental
OL,21,FPermitting Regulations 2016.
